#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga"
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 35. Satisutta → satosuttaṃ (bj) | sato (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Satisutta"
msgstr "35. Mindful"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.35:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn47.35:1.2"
msgid "“Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vihareyya sampajāno."
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant should live mindful and aware."

msgctxt "sn47.35:1.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī."
msgstr "This is my instruction to you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.35:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant mindful?"

msgctxt "sn47.35:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.35:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.35:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.35:2.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.35:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is mindful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.181"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.35:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant aware?"

msgctxt "sn47.35:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno viditā vedanā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, "
"viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant knows feelings as they arise, as they remain, and as "
"they go away."

msgctxt "sn47.35:3.3"
msgid ""
"Viditā vitakkā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "They know thoughts as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away."

msgctxt "sn47.35:3.4"
msgid ""
"Viditā saññā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"They know perceptions as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away."

msgctxt "sn47.35:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is aware."

msgctxt "sn47.35:3.6"
msgid "Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vihareyya sampajāno."
msgstr "A mendicant should live mindful and aware."

msgctxt "sn47.35:3.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti."
msgstr "This is my instruction to you.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.35:3.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
